               <ns1:Data format="json">{
    "In_Query": "Dear Support Team, I’m currently using the Cloud Data Integration (CDI) REST API V2 to monitor Secure Agent services as part of an automation tool. I’m building. While retrieving service statuses, I’ve noticed that services manually stopped by users are not included in the API response. From what I can see, the API returns services in states such as Running, Stopped, Deploying, Error, Need_Running, and Need_Stop. However, services that are manually stopped appear to be assigned a state of User_Stopped, which is not reflected in the API output. This results in an incomplete view of the service landscape and affects the accuracy of our monitoring and reporting. Could you please confirm whether this is expected behavior? If so, is there any workaround or alternative method to retrieve services in the User_Stopped state? We would like to ensure that our automation tool can display a comprehensive status of all services, including those that have been manually stopped. Looking forward to your guidance.",
